Posted by
Mary Joyce
Senior Talent Acquisition Specialist at RTB House
Send InMail
1000+ specialists, 80+ markets, 2000+ clients across EMEA, APAC and the Americas regions. Join RTB House - a global company that provides state-of-the-art marketing technologies for the top brands worldwide.

As a Business Analyst, you will play a crucial role in our success and the scalability of our campaigns. Using various data and analytical tools, you will analyze and report on campaign performance, providing recommendations for improvements and optimizations.

Are you a self-motivated individual who enjoys problem solving? Are you able to perform under pressure while prioritizing and managing multiple projects and clients in a fast-paced environment. If so, then this may be just the job for you!

What You Will Do
Comprehensive analysis to support Head-2-Head and Incrementality tests for our clients.
Create custom reporting and dashboards using SQL, Big Query, Google Data Studio and other analytical tools;
Perform statistical analysis of big data in R, Python or other programming tool;
Provide recommendations and verifying terms of A/B tests with clients;
Supervise technical setup of tests;
Recommend optimal methods of doing incrementality tests;
Analyze campaign performance and settings, and provide recommendations for improvements and optimization;
Work closely with our account managers to deliver high standards of customer service and reporting, including client-facing presentations;
Propose and develop solutions for tools and processes;
Provide research & analytical support for the complex cases in the account management team.

What We Are Looking For
Minimum of 2 - 4 years of experience working with business or data analytics;
Practical knowledge of Python, R or other analytical platforms;
Experience working with data visualization eg. in Tableau, Atleryx or similar;
Experience in collecting, analyzing, and effectively synthesizing data and information;
Experience presenting to clients or senior-level executives;
Strong problem-solving skills, curiosity to understand complex concepts;
Experience working with data processing and analytical tools (SQL, BigQuery, Google Data Studio);
Experience in statistical analysis and hypothesis testing;
Good knowledge of MS Office (Excel and PowerPoint in particular) or G Suite;
Proactivity, independence, ability to cooperate with different teams, good communication skills and time-management;
Self-motivation, initiative, high energy, detail orientation, thoroughness;
Ability to manage the process end-to-end and take ownership of the process or task.

Nice To Have
Practical knowledge of Google Scripts and Google Analytics;
Experience in project management;
Experience in process optimization;
Experience working in digital marketing or basic knowledge of retargeting.

Why RTB House
There are so many reasons you should choose RTB House. Here’s just a few…
You will have a direct impact on the success of the company. Your work matters and is essential to the evolution, growth and success of our business.
We’ve been recognized as one of the 2022 Best Places to Work by Built In NYC.
Built In NYC has also recognized us as one of the 2022 Best Paying Companies.
“Your Workspace. Your Choice.” Work from home, work from an office space, or blend the two together in a way that works for you. We’ll even provide you with a stipend to help set up your home office.
We prioritize your growth and career path with your goals and passions in mind.
Our training is comprehensive and continuous plus a stipend for external training
Extensive benefits package including 100% coverage of your medical insurance premium, matching 401K plan, baby cash, phone stipend and much more!
Fun events including coffee socials and virtual happy hours.
You will get to work with amazing people in one of the fastest growing sectors in online advertising.

About RTB House
RTB House is a global company that provides state-of-the-art marketing technologies for top brands and agencies worldwide. Its proprietary ad buying engine is the first in the world to be powered entirely by Deep Learning algorithms, enabling advertisers to generate outstanding results and reach their goals at every stage of the funnel.

Founded in 2012, the RTB House team comprises 1000+ specialists in over 30 locations around the globe. It serves more than 3,000 campaigns for clients across the EMEA, APAC, and Americas regions.

After successfully deploying Deep Learning into 100 percent of its algorithms in 2018, RTB House has continued its research in the field of AI. The AI Marketing Lab and Creative Lab were set up as new divisions of the company focused on inventing and advancing MarTech products. The company’s AI-based product offering includes retargeting solutions and branding campaigns with ultra-effective Video Ads.

